20--%20comes%20as%20Sunak%20seeks%20to%20capitalise%20on%20better%20economic%20data%20to%20woo%20voters%20hit%20by%20cost-of-living%20rises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHalving%20inflation%20within%20a%20year%20from%20historic%20highs%20of%20above%2011%20percent%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022%20was%20one%20of%20the%20former%20financier's%20five%20key%20pledges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20happened%20last%20year%20and%20on%20Wednesday%20rates%20slowed%20to%20a%20near%20three-year%20low%20at%202.3%20percent%20in%20March%2C%20prompting%20Finance%20Minister%20Jeremy%20Hunt%20to%20declare%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20proof%20that%20the%20plan%20is%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%2C%20in%20a%20Downing%20Street%20statement%20made%20in%20driving%20rain%20after%20he%20gathered%20his%20top%20ministers%2C%20said%20he%20had%20spoken%20to%20head%20of%20state%20King%20Charles%20III%20and%20requested%20the%20dissolution%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20king%20has%20granted%20this%20request%20and%20we%20will%20have%20a%20general%20election%20on%20July%204%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BNow%20is%20the%20moment%20for%20Britain%20to%20choose%20its%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20commentators%20have%20increasingly%20suggested%20that%20Sunak%2C%20trailing%20badly%20in%20the%20polls%20to%20the%20main%20opposition%20Labour%20party%2C%20could%20try%20to%20seek%20a%20bounce%20from%20the%20healthier%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20critics%20point%20out%20that%20is%20more%20to%20do%20with%20changes%20in%20the%20global%20economy%20than%20government%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20had%20previously%20batted%20back%20all%20efforts%20to%20name%20a%20date%2C%20saying%20only%20that%20he%20would%20go%20to%20the%20country%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeculation%20mounted%20again%20after%20Sunak%20and%20his%20top%20officials%20on%20Wednesday%20refused%20to%20deny%20fresh%20talk%20that%20he%20was%20about%20to%20call%20an%20election%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20more%20positive%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERumours%20went%20into%20overdrive%20when%20Foreign%20Secretary%20David%20Cameron%20was%20recalled%20from%20a%20trip%20to%20Albania%20and%20Defence%20Secretary%20Grant%20Shapps%20delayed%20a%20trip%20to%20eastern%20Europe%20to%20attend%20a%20cabinet%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHunt%20also%20cancelled%20a%20scheduled%20television%20interview%20for%20Wednesday%20evening%2C%20ITV's%20political%20editor%20said%2C%20as%20journalists%2C%20photographers%20and%20camera%20crews%20flocked%20to%20Downing%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUphill%20task%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economy%20--%20hit%20by%20external%20factors%20such%20as%20Covid%20and%20more%20self-inflicted%20wounds%20such%20as%20Brexit%20and%20former%20premier%20Liz%20Truss%20--%20will%20be%20a%20key%20battleground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Sunak%20faces%20an%20uphill%20task%20to%20convince%20the%20public%20that%20the%20country's%20finances%20are%20still%20safe%20in%20Tory%20hands%20after%2014%20years%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20has%20tried%20to%20steady%20the%20ship%20since%20succeeding%20Truss%2C%20whose%2049-day%20tenure%20ended%20after%20her%20unfunded%20tax%20cuts%20sent%20household%20bills%20soaring%2C%20spooked%20the%20markets%20and%20crashed%20the%20pound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmigration%20--%20another%20key%20issue%20since%20the%20government's%20vote-winning%20pledge%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20back%20control%26quot%3B%20of%20Britain's%20borders%20after%20Brexit%20--%20remains%20politically%20troublesome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20--%20the%20Tories'%20fourth%20leader%20since%202016%20--%20has%20talked%20tough%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20the%20boats%26quot%3B%20of%20irregular%20migrants%20crossing%20the%20Channel%20from%20northern%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20controversial%20scheme%20to%20deport%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda%20has%20yet%20to%20get%20off%20the%20ground%2C%20as%20costs%20and%20legal%20challenges%20mount.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResurgent%20Labour%2C%20under%20former%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%20has%20meanwhile%20been%20consistently%20ahead%20of%20the%20Tories%20by%2020%20points%20for%20almost%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20has%20sparked%20talk%20of%20a%20landslide%20similar%20to%20the%20first%20of%20Tony%20Blair's%20three%20election%20victories%20--%20and%20even%20a%20near%20wipe-out%20for%20the%20Tories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer%2C%2061%2C%20and%20his%20top%20team%20have%20in%20recent%20weeks%20been%20putting%20flesh%20on%20the%20bones%20of%20their%20election%20pitch%2C%20nearly%20five%20years%20after%20the%20party%20was%20thrashed%20by%20Boris%20Johnson%20and%20his%20vow%20to%20%26quot%3BGet%20Brexit%20Done%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Starmer%20set%20out%20six%20key%20pledges%20notably%20more%20electorally%20friendly%20than%20the%20hard-left%20policies%20of%20his%20divisive%20predecessor%20Jeremy%20Corbyn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer%2C%20a%20pro-European%20centrist%2C%20promised%20economic%20stability%2C%20shorter%20health%20service%20waiting%20times%20and%20a%20new%20border%20security%20command%20to%20tackle%20irregular%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20vowed%20to%20establish%20a%20publicly%20owned%20clean%20energy%20company%2C%20crack%20down%20on%20anti-social%20behaviour%20with%20more%20neighbourhood%20police%20and%20recruit%206%2C500%20new%20teachers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716396540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fpidepdgo_rishi-sunak-reuters_625x300_08_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frishi-sunak-ends-months-of-speculation-sets-july-4-as-elect